        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is conjectured from the likelihood that the information in the letter was communicated after the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4110.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal Society of London</ref> soirée on 28 April 1866 at which CD first met Turner (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5113.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to William Turner, 5 June [1866]</ref>). Subsequent correspondence with Turner is confined to medical topics relevant to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>, <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref>, and <hi rend="italic">Expression.</hi></note>
